“—reiterate your basic view that there can be little
                                                hope of peace and quiet in Europe if Berlin boils up
                                                into crisis periodically;

“—state your conviction that there ought to be
                                                improvements in the life of the West Berliners, if
                                                only on humanitarian grounds;

“—note the basic reality that the FRG feels intimate ties
                                                with the city and that there can be no thought of
                                                making it a third German state;
